<headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 24 at 6:12AM CST  by NWS San Angelo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of far southeastern
McCulloch, far northern Mason, and southwestern San Saba Counties
through 700 AM CST...
At 610 AM CST, radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Fredonia in far northern Mason County, moving quickly northeast at
45 mph.
HAZARD...Winds to 40 mph and half inch to penny size hail, along
with lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Minor
damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
San Saba, Richland Springs, Algerita, Fredonia, Sloan, Katemcy, Voca
and Harkeyville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
